    <section>
        <title>wrapper.pidfile</title>
        <para>
            File to write process ID to.  If set, a pid file will be written
            to the specified location when the Wrapper process is started.  The
            file will be deleted when the Wrapper process has terminated.
        </para>
        <para>
            In most cases, this property will not be set from within the
            <literal moreinfo="none">wrapper.conf</literal> file.  It can be
            passed to the wrapper process by shell scripts which require a
            specific pid file to control the shutdown of the Wrapper and its
            Java process.  An example can be found in the
            <literal moreinfo="none">sh.script.in</literal> file in the
            <literal moreinfo="none">src/bin</literal> directory.
        </para>
        <informalexample>
            <simpara><emphasis>Example:</emphasis></simpara>
            <screen format="linespecific"><![CDATA[wrapper.pidfile=/var/run/myapp.pid]]></screen>
        </informalexample>
    </section>
</chapter>
